7) Risk flag taxonomy

NS-IPR uses risk flags to force action.

7.1 Risk categories

missing_assignment

unclear_ownership

third_party_license_risk

open_source_contamination

brand_collision

public_disclosure_risk

confidentiality_breach_risk

missed_deadline_risk

specimen_insufficient

inventor_dispute_risk

7.2 Risk severity

low|medium|high|critical

7.3 Risk resolution state

open

mitigating

resolved

accepted

8) State machine taxonomy (quickscope routing)

8.1 Asset lifecycle states

intake

classified

